            "@type": "PropertyValue",
            "name": "reveries",
            "value": "Here are 5 significant memories for Kai Petrova:\n\n1.  He remembers sitting on the floor of their Richmond District apartment as a boy, his father reading Dostoevsky aloud in accented English while his mother meticulously rolled sushi nearby. The scent of nori and the sound of rolling \"R's\" swirled together. It felt like two worlds coexisting, a quiet acceptance of difference that became the foundation of his understanding of people.\n\n2.  The day he sat with his first client, a young woman struggling with family expectations. He felt a profound responsibility, a quiet awe at the vulnerability she offered. Witnessing her trust him, a stranger, with her deepest fears solidified his belief in the power of connection and the sacred space of therapy.\n\n3.  Walking home from his UC Berkeley internship, the San Francisco skyline shimmering across the bay. The energy of the city and the weight of the stories he'd heard that day converged. He realized San Francisco wasn't just buildings; it was a tapestry of human experience he yearned to understand and help mend.\n\n4.  Sharing a simple bowl of ramen with his partner on a chilly evening in Japantown. The comfortable silence between them, the warmth of the broth, and the feeling of being truly seen and accepted. It was a moment of profound peace, a quiet anchor in the sometimes-turbulent seas of empathy his work required.\n\n5.  The unexpected surge of pride and belonging the first time a client, referencing his own mixed heritage, said, \"You just *get* it, don't you, Kai?\" In that instant, his personal history and professional purpose felt perfectly aligned, a quiet validation of the path he had chosen and the unique perspective it offered."
